Question : 
How to make a Pascal Delay in Delphi ? 

Answer : 
Here is the code : (You can allso use Sleep(MSec), but its not so good) 

procedure delay(msec:longint); 
var 
 Start,Stop:longint; 
begin 
  start := gettickcount; 
  repeat 
  stop := gettickcount; 
  application.processmessages; 
  until (stop - start ) ›= msec; 
end; 
 
 

 
 
